-- Nestle Names Marco Settembri Head of Waters as Harris Retires
-- B y   T h o m a s   M u l i e r
-- 2013-09-23T06:38:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-23/nestle-names-marco-settembri-head-of-waters-as-harris-retires.html
Nestle SA (NESN) , the world’s biggest food
company, said  John Harris , the head of its bottled water
business, is retiring after 39 years and will be replaced by the
director of its petcare unit in Europe.  Marco Settembri, who joined Nestle 26 years ago, has helped
make the company’s petcare business one of its most profitable
in Europe, having led the division since 2007, the Vevey,
Switzerland-based company said in a statement today.  Harris will retire at the end of November and Settembri
will take over on Dec. 1, Nestle said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Thomas Mulier in Geneva at 
